User: C:\ai-execution-system>git status On branch main Your branch is ahead of 'origin/main' by 3 commits.   (use "git push" to publish your local commits) nothing to commit, working tree clean

Gemini: nothing to commit, working tree clean
This is also good news! It means:

You're on the main branch.
Your local main branch is now 3 commits ahead of the origin/main branch. origin/main is the remote version of your main branch (usually on GitHub, GitLab, etc.). This is expected because you've made local commits (the merge commit and possibly other commits from temp-orphan).
Your working directory is clean. No pending changes.
The next step is to "push" your local commits to the remote repository. This will update the origin/main branch with the changes you've made locally.

To do this, run the command Git is suggesting:

C:\ai-execution-system>git push
This command will upload your 3 local commits to the origin/main branch.

After running git push, your local main branch and the remote origin/main branch will be in sync.

Once you've run git push, you should be all done with the merge! Let me know if the git push command is successful or if you see any errors.
